<h2 id="capo-notes">Capo notes</h2>

<p>If you want to use the chords above and play along with John Denverâ€™s official version, youâ€™ll need a capo on the 2nd fret. Without a capo, youâ€™d need to use chords in the key of A to play along with John Denver (which makes a bit tougher, since a barre chord is needed for F#m). Otherwise, you can use no capo (using the chords I show) and youâ€™ll sound just fine on your own.</p>

<h2 id="understanding-the-timing-of-each-chord">Understanding the timing of each chord</h2>

<p>Weâ€™ll have 4 counts per measure. Chords are either played for 1 or 2 measures, depending on the part of the song. Hereâ€™s a look at the chord progressions used for each section. Everytime you see a chord name, play that chord for 4 counts (1 measure). If you see a slash (â€œ/â€), repeat the prior chord for an additional measure.</p>

